l\nbpRLAowEZXZlcpRLAowFZXZlcnmUSwKMBGV5ZXOUSwKMBGZhY2WUSwKMBGZpbmSUSwKMBWZpcnN0\nlEsCjAVmb3VuZJRLAowEZ2F2ZZRLAowDZ2V0lEsCjARnaXJslEsCjAJnb5RLAowFZ29pbmeUSwKM\nBGdvb2SUSwKMA2dvdJRLAowFZ3JlYXSUSwKMBGhhbmSUSwKMBWhhbmRzlEsCjARoZWFklEsCjAVo\nZWFyZJRLAowFaG91c2WUSwKMBGtub3eUSwKMBGxhc3SUSwKMBGxlZnSUSwKMA2xldJRLAowFbGln\naHSUSwKMBGxpa2WUSwKMBmxpdHRsZZRLAowEbG9uZ5RLAowEbG9va5RLAowGbG9va2VklEsCjAds\nb29raW5nlEsCjARtYWRllEsCjARtYWtllEsCjANtYW6USwKMBG1hbnmUSwKMA21heZRLAowFbWln\naHSUSwKMBm1vbWVudJRLAowEbXVjaJRLAowEbXVzdJRLAowFbmV2ZXKUSwKMB25vdGhpbmeUSwKM\nAm9olEsCjANvbGSUSwKMA29uZZRLAowGcGVvcGxllEsCjAdwZXJoYXBzlEsCjANwdXSUSwKMBXF1\naXRllEsCjAVyaWdodJRLAowEcm9vbZRLAowEc2FpZJRLAowDc2F0lEsCjANzYXeUSwKMA3NheZRL\nAowDc2VllEsCjAZzZWVtZWSUSwKMBHNlZW6USwKMA3NldJRLAowFc2hhbGyUSwKMCXNvbWV0aGlu\nZ5RLAowFc3RpbGyUSwKMBXN0b29klEsCjAhzdWRkZW5seZRLAowEdGFrZZRLAowEdGVsbJRLAowF\ndGhpbmeUSwKMBnRoaW5nc5RLAowFdGhpbmuUSwKMBnRob3VnaJRLAowHdGhvdWdodJRLAowEdGlt\nZZRLAowEdG9sZJRLAowEdG9va5RLAowGdHVybmVklEsCjAN0d2+USwKMBHVwb26USwKMAnVzlEsC\njAN3YXmUSwKMBHdlbGyUSwKMBHdlbnSUSwKMBXdoaXRllEsCjAd3aXRob3V0lEsCjAV3b3VsZJRL\nAowDeWVzlEsCjAN5ZXSUSwJoI0sBdYwFbWV0YXOUfZRoIEsDc3ViYXUu\n</properties>\n\t</node_properties>\n\t<session_state>\n\t\t<window_groups />\n\t</session_state>\n</scheme>\n\n\nThe above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangecanvas\\application\\outputview.py\", line 444, in __call__\n    self.handledException.emit((exc_type, exc_value, tb))\nSystemError: <method 'emit' of 'PyQt5.QtCore.pyqtBoundSignal' objects> returned a result with an exception set\n\nOriginal exception was:\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangecanvas\\scheme\\signalmanager.py\", line 1180, in __process_next\n    if self.__process_next_helper(use_max_active=True):\n       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangecanvas\\scheme\\signalmanager.py\", line 1218, in __process_next_helper\n    self.process_node(selected_node)\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangecanvas\\scheme\\signalmanager.py\", line 846, in process_node\n    self.send_to_node(node, signals_in)\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangewidget\\workflow\\widgetsscheme.py\", line 806, in send_to_node\n    self.process_signals_for_widget(node, widget, signals)\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangewidget\\workflow\\widgetsscheme.py\", line 820, in process_signals_for_widget\n    process_signals_for_widget(widget, signals, workflow)\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\functools.py\", line 909, in wrapper\n    return dispatch(args[0].__class__)(*args, **kw)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangewidget\\workflow\\widgetsscheme.py\", line 925, in process_signals_for_widget\n    handle_new_signals(widget, workflow)\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\functools.py\", line 909, in wrapper\n    return dispatch(args[0].__class__)(*args, **kw)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\orangewidget\\workflow\\widgetsscheme.py\", line 912, in handle_new_signals\n    widget.handleNewSignals()\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\Orange\\widgets\\unsupervised\\owhierarchicalclustering.py\", line 505, in handleNewSignals\n    self._update()\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\Orange\\widgets\\unsupervised\\owhierarchicalclustering.py\", line 619, in _update\n    self._set_displayed_root(tree)\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\Orange\\widgets\\unsupervised\\owhierarchicalclustering.py\", line 598, in _set_displayed_root\n    self._update_labels()\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\Orange\\widgets\\unsupervised\\owhierarchicalclustering.py\", line 654, in _update_labels\n    labels = [str(attr[i]) for i in indices]\n             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"C:\\Program Files\\Orange\\Lib\\site-packages\\Orange\\widgets\\unsupervised\\owhierarchicalclustering.py\", line 654, in <listcomp>\n    labels = [str(attr[i]) for i in indices]\n                  ~~~~^^^\nIndexError: tuple index out of range\n```\n\n\n\n**How can we reproduce the problem?** \n1. Corpus with `book-excerpts.dat`\n2. Preprocess Text\n3. Bag of Words\n4. Distances (Columns, Jaccard)\n5. Hierarchical clustering (Annotations: Name, but nothing appears)\n[no annotations.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/24496470/no.annotations.zip)\n\n\n\n\n**What's your environment?**\n<!-- To find your Orange version, see \"Help \u2192 About \u2192 Version\" or `Orange.version.full_version` in code -->\n- Operating system: Windows 10 x64\n- Orange version: 3.39.0\n- How you installed Orange: standalone installer\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@processo , thanks. According to git logs, I have committed this sin in the summer of 2017, without anybody noticing (or reporting) in 7.5 years.\n\nComputing Jaccard distances over columns of sparse matrix may not be as popular as one would (incorrectly!) expect. :)\n\nThe problem was not in clustering but in computation of distances. Other widgets would crash, too.\n> According to git logs, I have committed this sin in the summer of 2017, without anybody noticing (or reporting) in 7.5 years.\n\nActually no. @ajdapretnar did this two years later. I confess to have merged it, though (#3657).\n> Computing Jaccard distances over columns of sparse matrix may not be as popular as one would (incorrectly!) expect. :)\n\nApparently not. I ran into this in 2020 but used cosine (or transpose) instead. I felt it was time to report.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/biolab/orange3/commit/33aa9c1b776362285520d3fc82a61be61cc3bc4a", "https://github.com/biolab/orange3/commit/bca0013bb947a59e1988ecc8d9d26948fcd5753e", "https://github.com/biolab/orange3/commit/6a153d8429a5fcc152983bb6f12faa9fd7a3645c"], "created_at": "2026-02-25T21:44:22Z"}
{"repo": "biolab/orange3", "pull_number": 7241, "instance_id": "biolab__orange3-7241", "issue_numbers": [7240], "base_commit": "3d7660f530711049e2d9bddd757ec8fd0790abe1", "patch": "diff --git a/Orange/widgets/visualize/utils/plotutils.py b/Orange/widgets/visualize/utils/plotutils.py\nindex 08b9fcbe73b..ea0d2b17e49 100644\n--- a/Orange/widgets/visualize/utils/plotutils.py\n+++ b/Orange/widgets/visualize/utils/plotutils.py\n@@ -124,7 +124,7 @@ def __updateLayout(self):\n \n         self._label.setPos(label_pos)\n         self._label.setAnchor(pg.Point(*anchor))\n-        self._label.setRotation(-angle if left_quad else 180 - angle)\n+        self._label.setAngle(angle if left_quad else 180 + angle)\n \n         self._arrow.setPos(self._spine.line().p2())\n         self._arrow.setRotation(180 - angle)\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "FreeViz axis names don't show near 90\u00b0 angles\n<!-- \nThanks for taking the time to report a bug!\nIf you're raising an issue about an add-on (i.e., installed via Options > Add-ons), raise an issue in the relevant add-on's issue tracker instead. See: https://github.com/biolab?q=orange3\nTo fix the bug, we need to be able to reproduce it. Please answer the following questions to the best of your ability.\n-->\n\n\n**What's wrong?**\n<!-- Be specific, clear, and concise. Include screenshots if relevant. -->\n<!-- If you're getting an error message, copy it, and enclose it with three backticks (```). -->\nWhen axes in FreeViz are near multiples of 90\u00b0 their names are hidden.\n<img width=\"752\" height=\"630\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4b41fd78-3850-4888-8708-dd8a4ff97a27\" />\n\nThis is a composite image of angles when they appear.\n<img width=\"376\" height=\"314\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/78a60ecd-3ce8-4fab-a1e6-31c2a058d702\" />\n\n**How can we reproduce the problem?** \n<!-- Upload a zip with the .ows file and data. -->\n<!-- Describe the steps (open this widget, click there, then add this...) -->\n1. Paint data\n2. FreeViz\n3. Move axes inside 10\u00b0 offset of the four major directions\n\n**What's your environment?**\n<!-- To find your Orange version, see \"Help \u2192 About \u2192 Version\" or `Orange.version.full_version` in code -->\n- Operating system: Windows 10\n- Orange version: 3.39.0\n- How you installed Orange: standalone installer\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Thanks for diagnosing this! I've noticed that titles sometimes disappear, but haven't realized it is related to the angle.\n\nIt gets even better: the angle at which the text disappears depends on the length of the text -- longer text survives tighter angles. I speculate that transformation must change x and y for a certain amount, else something inside Qt crashes.\n\nLuckily, it seems that an alternative way to rotate the label (pyqtgraph's `setAngle` instead of qt's `setRotation`) works. I won't dig into why.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/biolab/orange3/commit/58e68e8bc9a6b560967ca49f37f89a3dd0d213b8"], "created_at": "2026-01-23T14:47:07Z"}
{"repo": "biolab/orange3", "pull_number": 7260, "instance_id": "biolab__orange3-7260", "issue_numbers": [7251], "base_commit": "ca7307d6c820782afb5bfc923d3d980c56cf3b3d", "patch": "diff --git a/Orange/widgets/unsupervised/owhierarchicalclustering.py b/Orange/widgets/unsupervised/owhierarchicalclustering.py\nindex 2421835269c..39231276b92 100644\n--- a/Orange/widgets/unsupervised/owhierarchicalclustering.py\n+++ b/Orange/widgets/unsupervised/owhierarchicalclustering.py\n@@ -442,7 +442,7 @@ def axis_view(orientation):\n         self.dendrogram.selectionChanged.connect(self._invalidate_output)\n         self.dendrogram.selectionEdited.connect(self._selection_edited)\n \n-        self.labels = TextListView()\n+        self.labels = TextListView(elideMode=Qt.ElideRight)\n         self.label_model = SelectedLabelsModel()\n         self.labels.setModel(self.label_model)\n         self.labels.setSizePolicy(QSizePolicy.Minimum, QSizePolicy.Preferred)\n@@ -652,7 +652,8 @@ def _update_labels(self):\n                 labels = [str(attr[i]) for i in indices]\n             elif isinstance(self.annotation, Orange.data.Variable):\n                 col_data = self.items.get_column(self.annotation)\n-                labels = [self.annotation.str_val(val) for val in col_data]\n+                labels = [self.annotation.str_val(val).replace(\"\\n\", \" \")\n+                          for val in col_data]\n                 labels = [labels[idx] for idx in indices]\n             else:\n                 labels = []\ndiff --git a/Orange/widgets/utils/graphicstextlist.py b/Orange/widgets/utils/graphicstextlist.py\nindex 2330df16300..efe24d6cd4d 100644\n--- a/Orange/widgets/utils/graphicstextlist.py\n+++ b/Orange/widgets/utils/graphicstextlist.py\n@@ -305,6 +305,11 @@ def __layout(self) -> None:\n             fm = QFontMetrics(font)\n             fontheight = fm.height()\n \n+        advance = cell_height + spacing\n+        self.__remove_items((self.__strip, ), self.scene())\n+        self.__strip = self.__color_strip(round(advance))\n+        offset = int(round(advance * 1.3)) if self.__strip else 0\n+\n         if self.__autoScale and self.__effectiveFont != font \\\n                 and self.data(0, Qt.FontRole) is None:\n             self.__effectiveFont = font\n@@ -312,17 +317,20 @@ def __layout(self) -> None:\n \n         if self.__elideMode != Qt.ElideNone:\n             if self.__orientation == Qt.Vertical:\n-                textwidth = math.ceil(crect.width())\n+                textwidth = math.ceil(crect.width()) - offset\n             else:\n                 textwidth = math.ceil(crect.height())\n             for row, item in enumerate(self.__textitems):\n                 text = self.data(row)\n-                textelide = fm.elidedText(\n-                    text, self.__elideMode, textwidth, Qt.TextSingleLine\n-                )\n-                item.setText(textelide)\n+                if text:\n+                    fmr = QFontMetrics(self.data(row, Qt.FontRole) or font)\n+                    textelide = fmr.elidedText(\n+                        text, self.__elideMode, textwidth, Qt.TextSingleLine\n+                    )\n+                    item.setText(textelide)\n+                else:\n+                    item.setText(text)\n \n-        advance = cell_height + spacing\n         if align_vertical == Qt.AlignTop:\n             align_dy = 0.\n         elif align_vertical == Qt.AlignVCenter:\n@@ -346,9 +354,6 @@ def __layout(self) -> None:\n                     crect.top() + i * advance + align_dy\n                 )\n \n-        self.__remove_items((self.__strip, ), self.scene())\n-        self.__strip = self.__color_strip(round(advance))\n-        offset = int(round(advance * 1.3)) if self.__strip else 0\n         if self.__orientation == Qt.Vertical:\n             self.__group.setRotation(0)\n             self.__group.setPos(offset, 0)\ndiff --git a/i18n/si/msgs.jaml b/i18n/si/msgs.jaml\nindex baa57fdad62..f63e4971b9d 100644\n--- a/i18n/si/msgs.jaml\n+++ b/i18n/si/msgs.jaml\n@@ -11676,6 +11676,8 @@ widgets/unsupervised/owhierarchicalclustering.py:\n             label_model: false\n             Enumeration: \u0160tevil\u010denje\n             Name: Ime\n+            \\n: false\n+            ' ': false\n             ', ': true\n         def `commit`:\n             items: false\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Hierarchical Clustering: replace newlines in annotations\n**What's wrong?**\nSometimes, annotations contain newlines, which results in overlapping labels in Hierarchical Clustering (perhaps elsewhere, too).\nIt would make sense to a) replace newlines with regular spaces and b) cut the annotation at X characters (only show first X characters).\n\n**How can we reproduce the problem?** \nUse any text data with newlines to annotate instances in HC.\n\n<img width=\"551\" height=\"603\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5a1f202a-40a4-49f7-bb64-6db0a7cc9ee4\" />\n\n**What's your environment?**\n- Operating system: OSX\n- Orange version: 3.40.0\n- How you installed Orange: dmg\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/biolab/orange3/commit/30deb0f4cd7f0c670fa4621454fdb85b912d6c9b", "https://github.com/biolab/orange3/commit/5ccaea3d75e313dbf39c2b6d09daab3d6f5974bf", "https://github.com/biolab/orange3/commit/48a8885b1d3eb36376681032f193260b7fc72e82"], "created_at": "2026-03-21T10:25:09Z"}
